        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 10:03PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1002 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Hereford, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hereford, Umbarger, Bootleg, Buffalo Lake, Dawn, and Simms.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
